body:
Thank you for putting together the docs!

@akshayrai Looks like Pinot moved away from Github wiki to readthedocs. see https://github.com/apache/incubator-pinot/wiki and  https://pinot.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html
We can weigh more on this offline.

Yes, I go around it by changing the line to :
URI uri = Paths.get(path).toUri();

Works for Windows and should be OS independent.

@kishoreg For most of the queries, removing the inter-segments limit won't add new keys because all the keys are common across segments. If keys are not common across segments, then the data is very skewed, thus limiting the key can give very wrong result.
Actually there are several use cases hitting this limit. With this change, at least we can guarantee consistent result running the same query.
The problem with @mayankshriv suggestion is that, as I mentioned, with the current semantic, we don't know how to define the bottom x% if there are multiple aggregations.
